{% extends "core/emails/base.html.j2" %}
{% block title %}
    {% if has_created_component %}
        Time to Upload Your First SBOM! - sbomify
    {% else %}
        Ready to Create Your First SBOM Component? - sbomify
    {% endif %}
{% endblock %}
{% block content %}
    {% if has_created_component %}
        <h1>Time to upload your first SBOM, {{ user.first_name|default:user.username }}!</h1>
        <p>
            Great job creating your first component! Now let's get to the exciting part - uploading your first SBOM to see what's inside your software and find any security issues.
        </p>
        <div class="progress-bar">
            <div class="progress-fill" style="width: 60%;"></div>
        </div>
        <p style="font-size: 14px; color: #64748b; text-align: center;">Your onboarding progress: 60% complete</p>
        <div class="highlight-box">
            <h3>What is an SBOM?</h3>
            <p>
                A Software Bill of Materials (SBOM) is like an ingredient list for your software.
                It shows all the parts, libraries, and pieces that make up your app, helping you find security problems.
            </p>
        </div>
        <h2>Why SBOMs Matter</h2>
        <ul class="feature-list">
            <li>Find security problems in your code automatically</li>
            <li>Meet government and industry requirements</li>
            <li>See what's inside your software</li>
            <li>Get alerts about new security issues</li>
            <li>Keep track of all your software parts</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="highlight-box">
            <h3>Don't Have an SBOM Yet?</h3>
            <p>No worries! We've made it incredibly easy to generate SBOMs automatically with our GitHub Action.</p>
            <div style="background: #f8fafc;
                        padding: 16px;
                        border-radius: 8px;
                        margin: 16px 0">
                <h4 style="margin-top: 0; color: #1e293b;">sbomify GitHub Action (Recommended)</h4>
                <p style="margin-bottom: 8px;">
                    Our official GitHub Action automatically generates and uploads SBOMs to sbomify with every push or release:
                </p>
                <ul class="feature-list" style="margin-bottom: 8px;">
                    <li>Zero-configuration SBOM generation for most languages</li>
                    <li>Automatic upload to your sbomify workspace</li>
                    <li>Integrates seamlessly with your existing CI/CD pipeline</li>
                </ul>
                <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 14px; color: #475569;">
                    We provide step-by-step setup instructions on the components page to get you started quickly.
                </p>
            </div>
            <p style="font-size: 14px; color: #64748b; font-style: italic;">
                <strong>Note:</strong> Already have SBOMs from other tools? You can upload them directly -
                we support SPDX and CycloneDX formats from any source.
            </p>
        </div>
        <h2>What Happens After Upload?</h2>
        <p>Once you upload your SBOM, sbomify will automatically:</p>
        <ul class="feature-list">
            <li>Check that your SBOM file is valid</li>
            <li>Read all the parts and pieces in your software</li>
            <li>Look for known security problems</li>
            <li>Create reports about what we found</li>
        </ul>
        <p style="text-align: center; margin: 32px 0;">
            <a href="{{ app_base_url }}/components/" class="button">Upload Your First SBOM</a>
        </p>
        {% if user_role == "owner" %}
            <div class="user-info">
                <strong>Workspace Owner Tip:</strong> Set up automatic SBOM creation in your
                build process. This keeps your SBOMs current with every new version.
            </div>
        {% endif %}
        <p>You're almost there! Upload your first SBOM to see what's in your software and find any security issues.</p>
    {% else %}
        <h1>Ready to upload your first SBOM, {{ user.first_name|default:user.username }}?</h1>
        <p>
            It's been a few days since you joined sbomify, and we wanted to check in!
            Let's get your first SBOM uploaded so you can start finding security issues in your software.
        </p>
        <div class="progress-bar">
            <div class="progress-fill" style="width: 25%;"></div>
        </div>
        <p style="font-size: 14px; color: #64748b; text-align: center;">Your onboarding progress: 25% complete</p>
