            </div>
            <p style="font-size: 14px; color: #64748b; font-style: italic;">
                <strong>Note:</strong> Already have SBOMs from other tools? You can upload them directly -
                we support SPDX and CycloneDX formats from any source.
            </p>
        </div>
        <h2>What Happens After Upload?</h2>
        <p>Once you upload your SBOM, sbomify will automatically:</p>
        <ul class="feature-list">
            <li>Check that your SBOM file is valid</li>
            <li>Read all the parts and pieces in your software</li>
            <li>Look for known security problems</li>
            <li>Create reports about what we found</li>
        </ul>
        <p style="text-align: center; margin: 32px 0;">
            <a href="{{ app_base_url }}/components/" class="button">Get Started with Your First SBOM</a>
        </p>
        {% if user_role == "owner" %}
            <div class="user-info">
                <strong>Workspace Owner Tip:</strong> Set up automatic SBOM creation in your
                build process. This keeps your SBOMs current with every new version.
            </div>
        {% endif %}
        <p>
            We believe in your success and want to help you get the most out of sbomify.
            Uploading your first SBOM is a big step toward making your software more secure!
        </p>
    {% endif %}
    <h2>Need Help?</h2>
    <p>If you're not sure where to start or have questions, we're here to help:</p>
    <p style="text-align: center;">
        <a href="{{ app_base_url }}/support/contact/"
           class="button button-secondary">Contact Support</a>
    </p>
{% endblock %}
{% block signoff %}
    <p>
        {% if has_created_component %}
            Keep up the great work!
        {% else %}
            We believe in your success and want to see you make the most of sbomify!
        {% endif %}
        <br>
        <strong>The sbomify Team</strong>
    </p>
{% endblock %}
